    <!-- OUR STORY (from PDF) -->
    <section class="section bg-darkgray">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <div class="section-label fade-up">Our Story</div>
        <div class="story-text fade-up">
          <p>
            In studying the history of revivals, Francis Frangipane noticed
            something striking: every revival was preceded by an organized
            prayer movement—except one. Curious, he asked the Lord why. The Lord
            replied,
          </p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; margin: 1.2em 0">
            “I answered the prayers of a million mothers.”
          </p>
          <p>
            In 1999, the Lord spoke to <strong>Papa Lou Engle</strong>, a
            prophetic father to a generation, with a defining question: "How can
            I turn America back to God?" That question set the trajectory for
            the next 25 years of prayer, fasting, and national repentance. In
            September 2000, after God miraculously provided for the work,
            400,000 young adults gathered on the National Mall in Washington,
            D.C. for a Joel 2-style solemn assembly of fasting and prayer.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: 1.5em">
            In 2024, that legacy crescendoed into the launch of
            <strong>A Million Women (AMW)</strong> on October 12, the Day of
            Atonement. Out of this divine moment, A Million Women Africa (AMWA)
            was born — under the continental leadership of
            <strong>Apostle Isi Igenegba</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- VISION & MISSION (two columns) -->
